00:27:43,420 --> 00:27:49,420
But the way to summarize it

567
00:27:49,420 --> 00:27:56,420
is in terms of the divergence of A.

568
00:27:56,420 --> 00:28:03,420
Let's look at the del dot A.

569
00:28:03,420 --> 00:28:05,420
That's the divergence of A.

570
00:28:05,420 --> 00:28:06,420
And let's look at,

571
00:28:06,420 --> 00:28:08,420
let's just take the simple case.

572
00:28:08,420 --> 00:28:10,420
The simple case, let's suppose

573
00:28:10,420 --> 00:28:12,420
there's only one mass point.

574
00:28:13,420 --> 00:28:15,420
If there's one mass point here,

575
00:28:15,420 --> 00:28:19,420
then let's look at the gravitational field

576
00:28:19,420 --> 00:28:21,420
in the neighborhood of that mass point.

577
00:28:21,420 --> 00:28:23,420
Well, it's pointing inward.

578
00:28:23,420 --> 00:28:25,420
If I take my mass,

579
00:28:25,420 --> 00:28:27,420
if I take my test mass

580
00:28:27,420 --> 00:28:29,420
and move it around in the vicinity

581
00:28:29,420 --> 00:28:31,420
of the heavy mass here,

582
00:28:31,420 --> 00:28:33,420
I'll discover a gravitational field

583
00:28:33,420 --> 00:28:35,420
which varies from point to point,

584
00:28:35,420 --> 00:28:38,420
always pointing toward that mass.

585
00:28:38,420 --> 00:28:40,420
So the gravitational field,

586
00:28:40,420 --> 00:28:42,420
the vector field points inward toward that point.

587
00:28:43,420 --> 00:28:46,420
The pointing, the inward pointingness of it

