00:29:54,420 --> 00:29:57,420
We take a small volume,

614
00:29:57,420 --> 00:29:59,420
count up all the mass in it,

615
00:29:59,420 --> 00:30:05,420
delta m over delta v is called the mass density,

616
00:30:05,420 --> 00:30:07,420
the mass per unit volume.

617
00:30:07,420 --> 00:30:10,420
And of course it varies in general from place to place.

618
00:30:10,420 --> 00:30:12,420
Here there's no mass,

619
00:30:12,420 --> 00:30:14,420
here there's mass per unit volume.

620
00:30:14,420 --> 00:30:16,420
Here there's mass per unit volume.

621
00:30:16,420 --> 00:30:20,420
So the mass per unit volume is itself a field.

622
00:30:20,420 --> 00:30:23,420
It's the density field.

623
00:30:23,420 --> 00:30:25,420
On the left hand side here,

624
00:30:25,420 --> 00:30:29,420
we have the divergence of A.

625
00:30:29,420 --> 00:30:31,420
The divergence of A,

626
00:30:31,420 --> 00:30:33,420
A is a vector field,

627
00:30:33,420 --> 00:30:35,420
but its divergence is a scalar.

628
00:30:35,420 --> 00:30:40,420
The relationship between masses and gravitational field,

629
00:30:40,420 --> 00:30:44,420
which is basically the relationship that Newton wrote down,

630
00:30:44,420 --> 00:30:45,420
here it is,

631
00:30:45,420 --> 00:30:48,420
can be re-expressed in the form

632
00:30:48,420 --> 00:30:53,420
that delta A is equal to minus

633
00:30:53,420 --> 00:30:55,420
4 pi, I'll tell you in a moment,

