In other words, the component,

813
00:39:41,420 --> 00:39:43,420
the perpendicular component of the field

814
00:39:43,420 --> 00:39:46,420
will be the same everywheres.

815
00:39:46,420 --> 00:39:51,420
It'll be pointing out with the same component

816
00:39:51,420 --> 00:39:53,420
everywheres on the sphere.

817
00:39:53,420 --> 00:39:56,420
So that means that the perpendicular component of A

818
00:39:56,420 --> 00:39:59,420
doesn't vary from point to point on the sphere,

819
00:39:59,420 --> 00:40:01,420
and that means that this integral here

820
00:40:01,420 --> 00:40:07,420
is just the perpendicular component,

821
00:40:07,420 --> 00:40:09,420
whatever it happens to be,

822
00:40:09,420 --> 00:40:11,420
times the integral of d sigma.

823
00:40:11,420 --> 00:40:14,420
What does the integral of d sigma mean?

824
00:40:14,420 --> 00:40:16,420
It's just the area of the sphere.

825
00:40:16,420 --> 00:40:19,420
It's just adding up all the little area cells of the sphere,

826
00:40:19,420 --> 00:40:21,420
and that's the area of the sphere

827
00:40:21,420 --> 00:40:23,420
which is four pi G.

828
00:40:23,420 --> 00:40:28,420
Four pi r squared.

829
00:40:28,420 --> 00:40:31,420
r here not being the radius of a planet,

830
00:40:31,420 --> 00:40:34,420
but being the distance from the center of the planet

831
00:40:34,420 --> 00:40:38,420
to the red sphere.

832
00:40:38,420 --> 00:40:41,420
Okay, so now you see why the four pi

833
00:40:41,420 --> 00:40:43,420
was in Gauss's law,

834
00:40:43,420 --> 00:40:45,420
why Gauss put it into his law.

835
00:40:45,420 --> 00:40:50,420
It was in order to be able to cancel that out at this point.

836
00:40:50,420 --> 00:40:51,420
It was arbitrary.

837
00:40:51,420 --> 00:40:53,420
You could have defined things differently.

838
00:40:53,420 --> 00:40:59,420
Now, we solve this for the gravitational field,

839
00:40:59,420 --> 00:41:01,420
and what does it tell us?

840
00:41:01,420 --> 00:41:04,420
It tells us that the gravitational field of a mass

841
00:41:04,420 --> 00:41:09,420
is minus mg over r squared.

842
00:41:09,420 --> 00:41:11,420
Something we already knew,

843
00:41:11,420 --> 00:41:13,420
that's Newton's law,

844
00:41:13,420 --> 00:41:17,420
that the acceleration due to a massive object

845
00:41:17,420 --> 00:41:21,420
is the mass of the object

846
00:41:21,420 --> 00:41:23,420
times G divided by r squared,

847
00:41:23,420 --> 00:41:25,420
but it gives us a nice,

848
00:41:25,420 --> 00:41:26,420
we talked about this last time,

849
00:41:26,420 --> 00:41:27,420
I'm just going back over it,

850
00:41:27,420 --> 00:41:30,420
it also tells us that it doesn't depend

851
00:41:30,420 --> 00:41:33,420
on the mass having all been concentrated at a point.

852
00:41:33,420 --> 00:41:35,420
All it depended on

853
00:41:35,420 --> 00:41:39,420
was the mass was spherically symmetrically distributed.

854
00:41:39,420 --> 00:41:41,420
Okay, so that's,

855
00:41:41,420 --> 00:41:45,420
I did this again to point out to you that

856
00:41:45,420 --> 00:41:49,420
del dot A equals minus four pi rho G

857
00:41:49,420 --> 00:41:51,420
is equivalent

858
00:41:51,420 --> 00:41:54,420
to A being the sum

859
00:41:54,420 --> 00:41:56,420
over all the mass points

860
00:41:56,420 --> 00:42:03,420
of Newton's characteristic expression for gravitational field.

861
00:42:03,420 --> 00:42:05,420
So that's cool, huh?

862
00:42:05,420 --> 00:42:07,420
It's a nice way to express things.

863
00:42:07,420 --> 00:42:11,420
This summarizes the very, very complicated equation

864
00:42:11,420 --> 00:42:12,420
on top of it.

865
00:42:12,420 --> 00:42:14,420
It doesn't look so complicated,

866
00:42:14,420 --> 00:42:17,420
but if you wrote it out for lots of mass points and so forth,

867
00:42:17,420 --> 00:42:19,420
it would become complicated,

868
00:42:19,420 --> 00:42:20,420
whereas here's a way to write it out.

869
00:42:20,420 --> 00:42:23,420
Here's a way to express it where it's rather simple.

870
00:42:31,420 --> 00:42:33,420
Yeah, while we're at it,

871
00:42:33,420 --> 00:42:35,420
somebody asked me last time

872
00:42:35,420 --> 00:42:39,420
about the gravitational field within the Earth.

873
00:42:39,420 --> 00:42:41,420
What is it like within the Earth?

874
00:42:41,420 --> 00:42:44,420
Here we did the gravitational field outside the Earth.

875
00:42:44,420 --> 00:42:47,420
We can now carry out a calculation

876
00:42:47,420 --> 00:42:49,420
of what's going on inside the Earth, if we like.

877
00:42:50,420 --> 00:42:53,420
It's kind of interesting.

878
00:42:53,420 --> 00:42:57,420
All we have to do now

879
00:42:57,420 --> 00:43:01,420
is take our red surface, same calculation,

880
00:43:01,420 --> 00:43:05,420
but now take the red surface inside the Earth.

881
00:43:05,420 --> 00:43:08,420
But now we have to be careful,

882
00:43:08,420 --> 00:43:10,420
because the amount of mass within the red circle,

883
00:43:10,420 --> 00:43:12,420
the red sphere,

884
00:43:12,420 --> 00:43:15,420
is not the total mass of the planet anymore.

885
00:43:15,420 --> 00:43:17,420
It's only the mass within the red sphere.

886
00:43:17,420 --> 00:43:19,420
So let's do the calculation over again.

887
00:43:20,420 --> 00:43:23,420
The right-hand side stays the same.

888
00:43:23,420 --> 00:43:26,420
The right-hand side is still 4 pi.

889
00:43:26,420 --> 00:43:29,420
In other words,

890
00:43:29,420 --> 00:43:32,420
the perpendicular component of the field

891
00:43:32,420 --> 00:43:34,420
times 4 pi times r squared,

892
00:43:34,420 --> 00:43:39,420
where this r is now the radius of the inner sphere here.

893
00:43:39,420 --> 00:43:43,420
What about the mass within the red sphere?

894
00:43:43,420 --> 00:43:46,420
How much mass is there within the red sphere?

895
00:43:46,420 --> 00:43:49,420
Well, for that, we have to make some kind of assumption

896
00:43:49,420 --> 00:43:53,420
about how the mass is distributed throughout the red sphere.

897
00:43:53,420 --> 00:43:55,420
Let's make the assumption,

898
00:43:55,420 --> 00:43:57,420
which is not so bad for the Earth,

899
00:43:57,420 --> 00:43:59,420
it's not a bad approximation for the Earth,

900
00:43:59,420 --> 00:44:03,420
that the mass density within the Earth is uniform.

901
00:44:03,420 --> 00:44:06,420
The mass density is uniform inside the Earth,

902
00:44:06,420 --> 00:44:08,420
and then when you get to the surface of the Earth,

903
00:44:08,420 --> 00:44:10,420
it drops abruptly to zero.

904
00:44:10,420 --> 00:44:12,420
That's not exactly true.

905
00:44:12,420 --> 00:44:15,420
It's denser near the center than near the outside.

906
00:44:15,420 --> 00:44:17,420
But let's take that as a model.

907
00:44:17,420 --> 00:44:19,420
A uniform mass density

908
00:44:19,420 --> 00:44:25,420
is the uniform mass per unit volume within the Earth.

909
00:44:25,420 --> 00:44:30,420
Then how much mass is inside this red region here?

910
00:44:30,420 --> 00:44:33,420
It's not the total mass of the Earth now.

911
00:44:33,420 --> 00:44:34,420
It's different.

912
00:44:34,420 --> 00:44:36,420
So let's calculate it.

913
00:44:36,420 --> 00:44:40,420
It's the volume of the sphere times the mass density.

914
00:44:40,420 --> 00:44:47,420
This is equal to minus the mass within the sphere

915
00:44:47,420 --> 00:44:50,420
and the mass within the sphere

916
00:44:50,420 --> 00:44:52,420
is the volume of the sphere,

917
00:44:52,420 --> 00:44:57,420
four-thirds pi r cubed.

918
00:44:57,420 --> 00:45:01,420
That's the volume of the sphere times rho.

919
00:45:09,420 --> 00:45:12,420
Four-thirds pi r cubed times rho.

920
00:45:12,420 --> 00:45:14,420
I think I got it right.

921
00:45:14,420 --> 00:45:16,420
Oh!

922
00:45:16,420 --> 00:45:18,420
On this side.

923
00:45:18,420 --> 00:45:21,420
G. Good. Thank you.

924
00:45:21,420 --> 00:45:23,420
All right, we can cancel out some things.

925
00:45:23,420 --> 00:45:26,420
We can cancel out the four pi's.

926
00:45:32,420 --> 00:45:35,420
And now we can divide by r squared.

927
00:45:35,420 --> 00:45:37,420
If I divide by r squared,

928
00:45:37,420 --> 00:45:43,420
what I get is a perpendicular is equal to minus one-third rho times g,

929
00:45:43,420 --> 00:45:46,420
one-third rho times g, times r.

930
00:45:46,420 --> 00:45:52,420
What does this say?

931
00:45:52,420 --> 00:45:56,420
This says that the acceleration of a test mass,

932
00:45:56,420 --> 00:46:00,420
of course, we would have to drill a hole through the Earth

933
00:46:00,420 --> 00:46:02,420
if we wanted to drop a particle.

934
00:46:02,420 --> 00:46:05,420
We can't drop particles if they're stuck in the rock.

935
00:46:05,420 --> 00:46:07,420
But if we had some sort of particle,

936
00:46:07,420 --> 00:46:10,420
well, either we drill a hole through the Earth and drop particles down,

937
00:46:10,420 --> 00:46:15,420
or we drop particles which don't interact with the material of the Earth.

938
00:46:15,420 --> 00:46:19,420
Neutrinos don't interact much with the material of the Earth.

939
00:46:19,420 --> 00:46:21,420
We drop a particle, what does it do?

940
00:46:21,420 --> 00:46:24,420
Well, it experiences an acceleration

941
00:46:24,420 --> 00:46:27,420
which is toward the center.

942
00:46:27,420 --> 00:46:29,420
That's the minus sign here.

943
00:46:29,420 --> 00:46:32,420
The perpendicular component of A is negative.

944
00:46:32,420 --> 00:46:34,420
That means it's toward the center.

945
00:46:34,420 --> 00:46:36,420
It's got some constants in it.

946
00:46:36,420 --> 00:46:39,420
Rho, g, and three. Those are just numbers.

947
00:46:39,420 --> 00:46:43,420
But it grows linearly with the distance from the center of the Earth.

948
00:46:43,420 --> 00:46:48,420
So it's an acceleration, which means a force.

949
00:46:48,420 --> 00:46:53,420
If I were to multiply this acceleration by the mass of the test particle on both sides,

950
00:46:53,420 --> 00:46:56,420
then I would have the mass on the test particle.

951
00:46:56,420 --> 00:46:59,420
The mass on the test particle is toward the center,

952
00:46:59,420 --> 00:47:03,420
and it's proportional to the distance away from the center.

953
00:47:03,420 --> 00:47:06,420
There's a name for such a system.

954
00:47:06,420 --> 00:47:09,420
It's a harmonic oscillator.

955
00:47:09,420 --> 00:47:12,420
A force which is proportional to distance.

956
00:47:12,420 --> 00:47:13,420
In other words,

957
00:47:13,420 --> 00:47:16,420
a particle displaced from the center

958
00:47:16,420 --> 00:47:20,420
will be pulled back to the center exactly as if it were on a spring,

959
00:47:20,420 --> 00:47:23,420
with a spring constant

960
00:47:23,420 --> 00:47:25,420
that depends on the mass density,

961
00:47:25,420 --> 00:47:27,420
depends on the gravitational constant,

962
00:47:27,420 --> 00:47:29,420
and it depends on three.

963
00:47:29,420 --> 00:47:31,420
So if we dropped a particle,

964
00:47:31,420 --> 00:47:33,420
if we drilled a hole through the Earth

965
00:47:33,420 --> 00:47:35,420
and dropped a particle,

966
00:47:35,420 --> 00:47:37,420
it would just oscillate up and down, up and down,

967
00:47:37,420 --> 00:47:39,420
like a harmonic oscillator.

968
00:47:39,420 --> 00:47:41,420
I forget the time constant.

969
00:47:41,420 --> 00:47:43,420
I think it takes about ten minutes for it to do that.

970
00:47:43,420 --> 00:47:44,420
I don't know.

971
00:47:44,420 --> 00:47:46,420
I think it takes about ten minutes for it to go through the Earth and come back,

972
00:47:46,420 --> 00:47:49,420
or something of that order of magnitude.

973
00:47:49,420 --> 00:47:54,420
So, and this is not important to the general theory of relativity.

974
00:47:54,420 --> 00:47:59,420
It's just another example of how to use Gauss's law and Gauss's theorem

975
00:47:59,420 --> 00:48:02,420
to solve what would be a very hard problem

976
00:48:02,420 --> 00:48:06,420
if we had to add up the contribution of every particle in the Earth.

977
00:48:06,420 --> 00:48:08,420
I mean, just think about it.

978
00:48:08,420 --> 00:48:10,420
How hard that would be.

979
00:48:10,420 --> 00:48:12,420
Yet this method allows us to solve it.

980
00:48:13,420 --> 00:48:16,420
It allows us to do it easily.

981
00:48:16,420 --> 00:48:17,420
Okay.

